\details{
The per-stratum RSE (relative standard error, equivalent to CV) is computed
with the finite-population correction (FPC):

\code{RSE_h = sqrt((1 - n_h / N_h) * s2_h / n_h) / ybar_h}

When \code{n_h = 1} for any stratum, \code{var()} cannot be estimated; RSE, DEFF, and
\code{meets_target} are set to \code{NA} for those strata and a warning is issued. The
function continues processing valid strata.

The per-stratum design effect (DEFF_h) compares the actual stratum variance
to the pooled-SRS variance baseline:

\code{DEFF_h = ((1 - n_h/N_h) * s2_h / n_h) / ((1 - n/N) * s2_overall / n)}

where \code{n = sum(n_h)}, \code{N = sum(N_h)}, and
\code{s2_overall = sum(N_h * s2_h) / sum(N_h)} (N_h-weighted pooled within-stratum
variance). The aggregate DEFF stored in \verb{$deff} is \code{Var_strat / Var_SRS}
(Cochran 1977).
}
